In [103]:
#Splitting train, test dataset
TrainDF, TestDF = train_test_split(df, test_size=0.35)
In [104]:
#Storing Label in a separate variable
Test_Label=TestDF["Decision"]
#Removing Label from the train set
TestDF = TestDF.drop(["Decision"], axis=1)
In [105]:
#Storing Label in a separate variable
Train_Label=TrainDF["Decision"]
#Removing Label from the test set
TrainDF = TrainDF.drop(["Decision"], axis=1)
In [106]:
# Create Decision Tree classifer object
clf = DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion= 'entropy') #using entropy as the criterion

# Train Decision Tree Classifer
clf = clf.fit(TrainDF,Train_Label)

#Predict the response for test dataset
y_pred = clf.predict(TestDF)
In [107]:
# Create Decision Tree classifer object
clf1 = DecisionTreeClassifier() #using the default criterion which is "gini"

# Train Decision Tree Classifer
clf1 = clf1.fit(TrainDF,Train_Label)

#Predict the response for test dataset
y_pred1 = clf1.predict(TestDF)
In [108]:
#calculating the accuracy of the Decision Tree model using Entopy
print("Accuracy of Decision Tree using Entopy:",metrics.accuracy_score(Test_Label, y_pred))

Accuracy of Decision Tree using Entopy: 0.9489795918367347

In [111]:
#resetting figure size
plt.figure(figsize=(100,100))
plot_tree(clf, #model
          feature_names = feature_names,  #features
          class_names = target_names, #labels
          filled = True, 
          rounded = True)
plt.title(label="Decision tree - Entropy ",
          fontsize=100,
          color="green")
